  "instructions": [
    "soak the dried white kidney beans in water for at least 8 hours or overnight.",
    "drain and rinse the soaked beans, then place them in a large pot or Dutch oven with the beef broth, water, carrots, beets, onion, garlic, kombu, dried dill weed, salt, and black pepper.",
    "bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 1 hour.",
    "add the apple cider vinegar and continue to simmer for another 30 minutes, or until the beans are tender.",
    "use an immersion blender to puree the borscht, or allow it to cool and puree it in a blender.",
    "taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "serve the borscht hot, garnished with a dollop of sour cream and chopped fresh dill if desired.",
    "refrigerate or freeze leftovers for up to 5 days or 2 months, respectively."
  ],
